	   <tr><td>Title:</td><td id=Sage colspan=1>Sage</td></tr>
	   <tr><td>Journal Rating:</td><td><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/star.gif><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/star.gif><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/star.gif><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/star.gif></td></tr><tr><td>Email:<td><a href=Mailto:Arjaizen@allakhazam.com>Arjaizen@allakhazam.com</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 id=headerrow>Bio:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=2>Arjaizen Izrhume, Wizard of Erudin –  Has a wry sense of humor, something not often expected from an Erudite… Cracks jokes often, even in combat… Highly intelligent by any standard save that of the casters of his own race, he was taunted as a child for being “slow”… Prefers the company of Barbarians to that of other Erudites, as a result of that childhood taunting… Respects the individual strengths of other races… A master blacksmith, baker, fisherman, swimmer, and "combat medic"… Fluent in the languages of barbarians, humans, erudites, elves, dark elves, dwarves, and gnomes… 

Most stories in my journal are dramatizations of real events during EQ.  Characters referred to by name in those stories are real, though may on occasion have their names changed.  Characters not belonging to me are used by permission of their players when their names are unchanged.

If you should read my journal, please rate it.  </td></tr></table></td></tr></table></center>
