	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=101948908629599>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=101948908629599>Mote:  Behind the Scenes</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=101948908629599#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Apr 22nd 11:31 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Sage>Arjaizen</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>197 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.81]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Thank you for your kind words.<br><br>When I joined the Fallen Wolves a couple of weeks ago, we almost immediately formed a group of level 30-ish folks for what we called a &quot;wolf pack&quot;.&nbsp;&nbsp;I wanted to write a story about our adventures, but couldn't think of a &quot;hook&quot; for it.  When we decided our first pack hunt would be in Sol A, I was chatting with the woman that plays the cleric Ahmai, and she suggested that perhaps the pack might be going on a rescue mission.  <br><br>The idea of the pack hunt appealed to more folks than we intended, and rather than six of us, closer to ten showed up the night of our mini-raid, including the level 45 warrior Ainer.  Well, Ainer was too high in levels for the hunt, and we had decided that the original six members of the pack should group together, so the others decided to leave... but not before Apalonia got killed.  So, Ahmai rezzed her, and I used that as the hook for giving most of the &quot;extras&quot; a graceful exit.<br><br>A couple of players were in and out during the night, so that's why if you count carefully, you'll see that there's more than six party members at the end of the story.  Also, Crystal didn't exist, she was a plot device.  Still, there was a lot of &quot;reality&quot; to it.<br><br>- Arjaizen making Bristal some plate armor immediately before we went in.<br><br>- Alerivers unexpectedly joining us.<br><br>- Bristal being the last to arrive.<br><br>- Apalonia's death and resurrection.<br><br>- The recovery of the Heart of Fire<br><br>- Crushor's surprise arrival (sans splintering door. ;-)<br><br>- The nightmarish overpull leading to the emergency evac<br><br>- Goldiggin passing out as he completed the evac spell, and Bristal's LoH to bring him back as the spell took effect.  (I'm still a bit fuzzy on this miracle, but facts are facts)<br><br>-Appearing at the so-called &quot;safe point&quot;, only to find ourselves in the middle of someone else's train.<br><br>- Crushor's last stand (he blocked the tunnel so we could all zone.)  Ahmai and Goldiggin zoned back to heal him, and he dinged killing the last goblin in the train.<br><br>&quot;Mote&quot; is the first of what I hope will be a series of Wolf Pack adventures.  I'm glad you enjoyed it.  </p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>40th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
