	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Sage>Arjaizen</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>197 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.79]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Friends:<br><br>You will note that the title of this journal has changed.&nbsp;&nbsp;As of last night, I no longer belong to the 7th Legion, a guild I belonged to for about a year and a half, and served as an officer for the past six months.  <br><br>The 7th was a once-thriving guild, and I very much enjoyed the company of its members.  However, about a year ago, many long-time members started to drift away.  I would often find myself the only member online for days at a time.  Rarely was there more than two other members on.<br><br>A restructuring of the officers didn't help much.  The old officers still didn't come on much, either to other RL commitments, or fascination with other on-line games.  As a new officer, I had hopes of helping to turn things around, but folks I invited in would play for a few sessions, see a maximum of one or two members, and would quickly quit for a more active group.<br><br>After a year of waiting, hoping, warning, and trying, I finally decided it was time to go elsewhere, as one of the most fun parts of guild membership is enjoying the fellowship of the other members... a pleasure I have not enjoyed for a long time.<br><br>Still, I left the 7th with a good deal of sadness, and there are a number of good people I am sure I am disappointing.  To the remaining members of the 7th Legion, I offer my apologies for my departure, and my good wishes for the future.  Most especially, I give my thanks to Fortenbras, Biffington, Carza, Sedusa, and last but not least, Dracoius Tyr for allowing me the honor of being included as one of you.<br><br>Last night, I became a member of the Fallen Wolves.  During the past few months, I have had the pleasure of adventuring with a good number of the Wolves, and was impressed by their abilities and by their tendency to &quot;hunt in packs,&quot; something I really never got the chance to do in the 7th.  In trying to find a new place to call home, the quick friendships I found made the Fallen Wolves a natural choice.<br><br>So from now on, &quot;Tales of the 7th Legion&quot; has become &quot;Tales From the  Nameless,&quot; the server on which I play.<br><br>Fare well, and good hunting, friends.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>40th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
