	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=101527535648061>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=101527535648061>For those who have wondered...</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=101527535648061#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Mar 4th 3:57 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Sage>Arjaizen</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>197 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.79]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>No, I haven't fallen off the face of Norrath.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then again, since I am spending my days on Luclin of late, perhaps I have. :-)<br><br>It seems the writing muse has left me temporarily, as there are no fresh ideas in my head at the moment.  This is probably not all that bad a thing, as the pressures of RL have been quite heavy in the past six weeks or so, and I have had little time for creative writing as it is.<br><br>What free time I do have, I have spent in playing EQ, rather than writing about it.  I've been giving some thought to putting together a story that revolves around my adventures in Luclin, which at this point have centered on Shadow Haven, Paludal Caverns, and the Netherbian Lair.<br><br>Stay tuned. :-)</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>40th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
