	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=10147594926552>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=10147594926552>Greetings to you too!</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=10147594926552#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Feb 26th 4:38 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=76256><span id=Sage>Gorfrey Defender of Justice</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>63 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Dear sir,<br><br>Please accept my humble and sincere apology for not having responded to your letter sooner.&nbsp;&nbsp;I only recently returned to Kaladim after a long absence.  I was handed your letter by Gunlok Jure when I arrived in Underfoot Citadel just yesterday.<br><br>I too am regarded as something of an anomaly by my own people.  After all, how many dwarves do you know that can write and spell like me?  Although I am sure he would disagree, General Jyleel Vad has largely succeeded in making a more polished paladin of me.  Not quite up to the standards of high elves or Erudites, but certainly better than your average dwarf, who can hardly make a complete sentence.  I even bathe every day, once I discovered... well, that is another story altogether.  Ahem.  <br>At any rate, my fellows still hold me in high esteem although they certainly have some difficulty understanding me from time to time.<br><br>Yes, I agree, the sand giants of the Northern Desert of Ro are not to be trifled with.  I only recently had the unpleasant experience of getting fairly close to one, but apparently he did not notice me.  I later had the opportunity to examine him up close when a large group of powerful warriors and casters slew him.  I had thought barbarians and ogres were large, but this being was absolutely huge.<br><br>Well, I hope you will have the time and opportunity to write again.  Please let me know if you wish me to contribute to your literary works.<br><br>Fare thee well!  Brell travel with thee!<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Feb 26 16:40:13 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Gorfrey Bellhewer, <br>Knights of Shining Light<br>Paladin of the 54th Quest, <br>Zebuxoruk Server</td></tr>
