	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Sage>Arjaizen</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>197 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>/ooc on<br><br>Sorry folks, RL has been a bear of late.&nbsp;&nbsp;Little time to write, or even to keep up with the adventures of my friends here in Allakhazam's realm.  I hope this will change soon.  Don't worry, I'm not done yet. :-)<br><br>/ooc off<br><br>---<br><br>Dear Euara:<br><br>I know I have been remiss with my correspondence of late, but I've had much to do in working on my smithing, and have been doing a good deal of research on spells.  Sadly, I've not been able to devote much time to writing.  For this I apologize.<br><br>Your brother has been very busy.  He recently escorted the clerics of Quellious to High Keep and back for a council meeting of the good allied deities.  I won't bore you with the details of the council, but suffice it to say that your brother acquitted himself well, and has redeemed himself in the eyes of Depnar Bulrious, whom he had previously disappointed somewhat.<br><br>After the meeting was over, he returned to Odus, and back to The Warrens, where he continued his crusade against the kobold hordes.<br><br>I am concerned for him however.  It seems he has attracted the attention of both the King of the Trolls, and The Queen of the Iksar.  I can only pray that they find more pressing concerns to deal with, as I fear for his safety should they not.  Thus far, he has either avoided or successfully dealt with the challenges they have laid before him, but I do not know how much longer his good fortune will hold out.<br><br>Recently, he got through the Warrens, and is now fighting the more powerful kobolds in the Stonebrunt Mountains.  As of last night, he was awarded his 23rd rank, and has surpassed his father, who is still of the 22nd Circle.  Perhaps there is a virtue to single-minded focus.<br><br>I hope this note finds you well, my dear.  Fare well, and good hunting.  Be careful.<br><br>Your loving father<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Jan 29 12:01:33 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>40th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
