<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f10093778492596>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=10093778492596>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=10093778492596>Know Thine Enemies, part 5</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=10093778492596#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Dec 26th 9:44 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Sage>Arjaizen</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>197 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Depnar Bulrious, Guild master of the Peacekeepers, looked up from his desk when Bejaizen entered his office and stood at attention.&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;Bejaizen&quot; he said, &quot;perhaps I have my days confused.  Today -is- the day you were supposed to be on the morning boat to Qeynos, is it not&quot;<br><br>Bejaizen's expression tensed. &quot;Aye sir, it is.  I missed the boat.  I have no excuse&quot;<br><br>&quot;That boat was the last one to get you to Qeynos in time to reach the council meeting.  The clerical ambassador left on it.  Without, I might add, the full Peacekeeper escort he was -supposed- to have.&quot;  Bulrious stood and as he began pacing the room, continued: &quot;With the troubling news of an Iksar/Troll alliance, one might think that appointed escort would consider it somewhat important to BE on that boat, wouldn't you think?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Yes, sir,&quot; Bejaizen answered.  He wondered if there would be any great objection if he just jumped into The Hole and got it over with?<br><br>&quot;You should have come back to Erudin at least a day earlier,&quot; Bulrious added.  &quot;I emphasize the words 'at least.'  Your irresponsible actions could have jeopardized Erudite involvement in the council.  Fortunately, our ambassador went with the Prexus delegation, so there will be at least some capable swordsmen with him.&quot;<br><br>The paladin commander's expression softened slightly.  &quot;However, the fact that you didn't come back earlier meant you were there to save Sentinel Creot when he would otherwise have certainly died.  The priests tell me he will need some rest for a few days, but will recover fully.  For that I'm grateful.  Creot is a good man, and I would hate to lose him.<br><br>&quot;However, that bit of good fortune does not excuse your otherwise poor judgment.  Were you not specifically asked for by the Koada Dal cleric Icewind, I'd leave you on guard duty in the palace prison for a month at least.&quot;  He grimaced slightly, and added, &quot;As it is, I had to call in a favor from Ghanlin Skyphire.  One of the Crimson Hands will Port you to the wizard spires of North Karana.  From there, you will travel north and meet with the delegation at the gypsy camp near the guard tower.&quot;<br><br>Bejaizen considered that.  Skyphire was the Guild master of the Crimson Hands, the most powerful group of wizards on Norrath, of which his father Arjaizen was a member, if not one in all that good standing.  The Crimson Hands were, for the most part, worshippers of Solusek Ro, not Quellious, and cared little for the needs of the Church of the Tranquil.  He wondered what kind of favor he owed Lord Bulrious that he would pull one of his wizards to perform such a menial task on short notice?<br><br>&quot;You will leave tomorrow morning, so get yourself prepared,&quot; the Guild master ordered.  &quot;And Bejaizen?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Yes, sir?&quot;<br><br>&quot;DON'T mess this up.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Aye, sir. By your leave?&quot;<br><br>Lord Bulrious sat back at this desk and started writing.  Without looking up, he said, &quot;Dismissed.&quot;<br><br>Bejaizen closed the door behind him, and let out a sigh of relief.  It could have gone far, far worse.  <br><br>---<br><br>Bejaizen, of the Clan Izrhume<br>19th Rank Paladin of Quellious<br>7th Legion, The Nameless<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Dec 26 10:06:35 2001</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>40th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
