<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f100605332044089>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=100605332044089>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=100605332044089>In the Gorge - Ch. 4: Call to Arms</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=93845&mid=100605332044089#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Nov 17th 10:15 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Sage>Arjaizen</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>197 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The two adventurers peered carefully over the rock, watching the evil eye and two minotaurs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The horned giants stood mesmerized by the floating orb, while an animated sword and shield, the "pet" of the eye, drifted about the area, as though on patrol.<br><br>"I don't like it," Cona grumbled.  "Those eyes never do much with any but themselves.  Why is that one so interested in those minotaurs?"<br><br>"Communicating, most likely," Barrik answered.  "The eyes don't talk.  Their voices just kind of ring through your head."<br><br>The big shaman's eyes narrowed. "How'd you know that?"<br><br>"One charmed me once.  I was lucky that someone else attacked it and managed to distract it enough that I could break the spell.  A scary thing," Barrik said, "not being able to control your own arms and legs."<br><br>"Aye, it would be," Cona muttered in agreement.  He pointed off in the distance, where a small, pale bluish-green humanoid approached. "Look.  A goblin's coming this way."<br><br>"What is this, a summit meeting?  This could be important to our mission.  I'm going to try for a closer look," the ranger said, as he cast a spell of camouflage and slowly snuck his way closer to the group.<br><br>Several tense minutes passed as Cona watched and waited for his friend to return.  As he watched, the goblin's arms began to wave, and an eerie light surrounded him.  Cona recognized the translucent haze coalescing around the goblin as a wizard's spell of shielding.  A moment later, Barrik appeared out of nowhere, whispering "Let's go... quietly."<br><br>...<br><br>They waited about a ten-minute walk from where they had spied the meeting.  This was the way back to Runnyeye, and they felt certain the wizard would return down the same ravine.  A short time later, they heard it approach.  Waiting for the goblin to pass (for they didn't want it to flee back towards the evil eye,) they prepared their ambush.  <br><br>Once it was past, Barrik spoke arcane words, and roots grew from the ground, entangling and starting to crush the goblin's spindly legs.  Cona spoke in a similar though slightly different tongue, and a freezing blast of icy shards slashed at the wizard, preventing it from getting off its own counter spell.  As it readied another spell, Barrik let fly an arrow, which buried itself in the goblin's throat.  As the roots slowly withdrew from the pale corpse&#8217;s legs, it crumbled to the rocky ground.<br><br>Searching the body for evidence, they found a paper.  "What does it say?" Cona asked.<br><br>I don't know.  I don't recognize the language," Barrik replied.  "We'd best get this back to the Mayor's office in Rivervale.  Perhaps someone there can make it out."<br><br>Hiding the corpse in a crevice, they quickly and quietly made their back to the home city of the halflings.<br><br>...<br><br>"Oh dear, oh dear," Gobo Furryfoot wailed.  "This is terrible.  Most terrible."<br><br>Mayor Gubbin of Rivervale looked at his chief linguist and asked, "What's terrible?"<br><br>"The goblins," came the response. "There are at least three times what we thought.  We'll never stop them ourselves, never!  And they are planning an offensive, in seven days time!"<br><br>The Mayor turned to the Ranger of the 7th Legion and the Barbarian of Halas.  The weariness had darkened his face, leaving him looking haggard and tired.  He said, "Then we are lost.  Thank you for your help, we will evacuate our old, infirm, and children as best we can. The rest of us will try and at least make the goblins feel they have paid a price for our homes."<br><br>Barrik looked at the floor and let out a long sigh.  Then he straightened up, and with steely eyes asked the Mayor, "Do you know how the 7th Legion came to be?"<br><br>Nodding his head slowly, the Mayor replied, "The Legion of legend died to a man, defending Halas from a gnoll invasion."<br><br>"Yes.  And the Legion of the present, if necessary, will die to a man defending Rivervale," the Legionnaire promised.  "There is a line beyond which evil has not, can not, and WILL not cross.  WE are that line.  If you but ask, Mister Mayor, the Legion will come."<br><br>Gubbin considered the graying ranger and for the first time in weeks, it seemed as though the weight on his shoulders had been lessened.  "Bring your Legion... and thank you."<br><br>--------------------------------<br><br>To: Fortenbras Oberonis, Caesar<br>From: Barrik Moonhunter, Legionary<br>Re: A Call to Arms<br><br>Hail, Caesar!<br><br>I bring bad tidings.  The forces of the goblins in Runnyeye are far stronger than the halflings of Rivervale expected, or can hope to defeat.  The Mayor of Rivervale has requested the further aid of the 7th Legion in fighting the evil horde.<br><br>Intelligence I have been able to gather indicates that the unholy alliance between the goblins of Runnyeye and the minotaurs of the Gorge of King Xorbb may have been facilitated by the King of the Gorge's Evil Eyes.  It may be that the eyes feel their present domains are too small, and wish to expand their power.  Since they appear to be enchanters of no small power, this is of great concern.<br><br>I request that the Caesar, the Marshall of War, and the Council authorize a raid on the Runnyeye Citadel, so this scourge of central Antonica may be beaten back into submission.  Further, that some of our most powerful Legionnaires enter the Gorge of King Xorbb with the intent of slaying the leadership of the evil eyes, thereby striking at the heart of the goblin/minotaur alliance.<br><br>To the Glory of the 7th!<br><br>In service to Karana,<br><br>Barrik Moonhunter, Legionary<br>C/O League of Antonican Bards, Rivervale<br><br>--------</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>40th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
